        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "Notes\n- β1 definition: [ML]/([M][L]) for the reaction Fe³⁺ + L ⇌ FeL (no H⁺ or OH⁻ terms; no polynuclear species).\n- The Fe³⁺–EDTA complex is ~9 log units more stable than Fe³⁺–NTA at 0.1 M ionic strength. Both constants decrease at higher ionic strength, but EDTA remains much stronger—consistent with its higher denticity (hexadentate) and stronger chelate effect compared to NTA (tridentate).",
